Type: Package
Package: LLMRagent
Title: Agents, Multi-Agent Conversations, and Agent Experiments for R
Version: 0.7.1
Authors@R:
    person("Ali", "Sanaei", , "sanaei@uchicago.edu", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Build language-model agents in R on top of the 'LLMR' package:
  agents with personas, native tool calling, pluggable memory, and hard
  budgets; multi-agent conversations with shared transcripts and turn-taking
  policies (debates, focus groups, interviews, deliberations with votes);
  factorial agent experiments run in parallel with seeds and tidy results;
  and an orchestrator that pairs one strong model with many cheap workers.
  Every run produces a tidy transcript and a trace of calls, tokens, and
  timings, so agent-based studies are inspectable and reproducible.
